<br>
<br>
1. The book club.<br>
In my opinion this was originally a good thought.<br>
However I have to say that I strongly dislike the way this was done, secrecy is in no way a good way to do it. <br>
<br>
Its as simple as this:<br>
A guild is a wholeness.<br>
Officers are picked because off skills, experience and the devotion that they can offer to that guild. Is an officer worth more than a regular member or any member worth more than other members? No, not in any way. And im sure EVERYONE agrees. <br>
<br>
The secret post was made to discuss the &quot;idea&quot; of the bookclub as far as i understood.<br>
How is it that i feel, afther reading those posts, that i have been left out of the wholeness... out of something that concern me as much as any other member.<br>
Im not talking about the discution of how to make it work<br>
-&gt; <br>
some ppl come up with an idea and want to form the idea together to get something to propose to the rest, just like chatting. Ok, I dont mind it.<br>
<br>
What I do mind and what im talking about is the &quot;elections&quot; &quot;votes&quot; &quot;choosing&quot; &quot;picking&quot; &quot;evaluating&quot; of people.<br>
<br>
Those things are a guildissues, not an internal officer discution and not an internal friends discution.<br>
Thats just the way it is and should be in a guild, thats why im in the guild and not just in a channel called viatores wher i can chat.<br>
<br>
Meaning nothing else than I think that was wrong, it could have been done better.<br>
<br>
<br>
2.<br>
Making objections  to something is useless without offering a another solution. And here is my idea:<br>
<br>
Preplanned grouping is a good idea, but rather than creating the groups and  choosing/picking the ppl to attend and to lead..<br>
get back to the old system of weekly grinds, and add some improvements. <br>
The guild has many officers.. take some more use of those officers who want.(If no officers want, it doesnt mean a dedicated player cant do this)<br>
Put one or two officers who would like to do this in charge of :<br>
Putting up a weekly location fer each lvl group. &lt;<br>
10-20, 20-30, 30-40, 40-46, 46+ <br>
<br>
Place a locked post in the event section if possible, containing that weeks locations with lvls. When the week is over, itl be the officer in charge who will set up some new locations and lvls, remove the old post and add a new post. (ther is allways places not everyone knows of and its that persons responsability to read on eq atlas and other zone guides to  find appropriate places.<br>
<br>
Also.. might post something on the allies boards about this beeing a system that we use, and they should feel free to drop by.<br>
<br>
Locations isnt that important people, the location is not what makes it fun.. its the ppl ur ther with.<br>
Also, try beeing open minded. If 7 ppl show up on a location..that doesnt mean u ask someone to leave.. it means u divide the groups up and work it out.Thats what a friends are for..making things better.<br>
<br>
I posted this somewher else aswell, and a reply i got from someone,i think it was Zapo, is that it limits the choices fer a week. Thats a fair answer Zapo, but in my opinion its wrong. The weekly grindspot never was ment to force ppl to those locations, it was just an offer to wher ppl might go together.<br>
Preplanned weekly grinds doesnt mean ppl must go to those locations, ppl will have to be open minded. It isnt worse than logging on and asking in guildchat if the ppl in your lvl range went to the preplanned location, or if they went some other place wher you might join them.It isnt worse than 4 ppl meeting at the grindspot and saying.. ok..this is becoming a bit boring..lets head to Sebelis instead..and when ppl log on we tell them we went ther instead so they can come join us.  <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Like everything else in life, the game is what YOU make of it.<br>
<br>
<br>
Noone else can tell you what to do and how to do it. <br>
<br>
<br>
YOU make your choices.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
I actually suggest that the posts about the secrecy.. the posts about the book club and the posts regarding the same issue.. and any offending post please <br>
be removed. <br>
<br>
It is not too late to put bad things behind us and look forward to a bright future in the guild together with our friends.<br>
<br>
It is not too late for those who have left to come back, you have all said it.. we love you.. we wish you well.. we still want to keep in contact..but we are leaving.<br>
It is true.. you love the guildies.<br>
End of discution..come back to us, prove that you too are willing to put this behind you and look towards a nice time with the people that you love. <br>
<br>
<br>
Truth be, everyone cant get along.. everyone can make mistakes.. everyone can missunderstand.. everyone can get angy.. and EVERYONE has every right to do so.<br>
<br>
We are all in this guild because we like eachother, not because the guild is old and honorable. Because we Love beeing together, and we allways have.<br>
<br>
For as long as i have been in this guild, nothing like this has ever been made sutch an issue, and ther is honestly no reason it should.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
I want you to think of what i wrote.. i want you to think of what you want.. not what other wants... and i want you to repeat within..... <br>
The game is what I make of it.<br>
<br>
<br>
Love and the highest respect to every member of Viatores.<br>
<br>
Zecola Nitka, Dien, Leres, Midgy, Alkazem soulmender, syenia Sparklingsky, <br>
Sometimes also Valdraug, Aquinas, Alore.<br>
<br>
.......If everyone got along perfectly ...............<br>
.......evolution as we know it would stop..........<br>
<br>
<br>
*pulls the plug* im off to bed.<br>
